THE GREAT WALL OF CHINA
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad
In the mountains north of Peking (Beijing), looking toward Inner Mongolia, is the Great Wall. The largest
man-made structure on earth, the 3,000 mile wall was begun in the third centur B.C. It took ove
ZUU years to complete. The Peking area also offers such wondrous sights as the Ming Tombs, the
Forbidden City, the Great Hall, Chairman Maos Memorial and the lemple of Heaven. Shanghai
Soochow (Suzhou), Hangchow (Hangzhou), and Canton (Guangzhou), among many other cifies,
offer equally breathtaking vistas
A visito the People's Republic of China is a unique and totally remarkable experience; now, only
14 hours away on Pan Am's 747SP Clippers
